Pegasos II Firmware — license summary
======================================

This project combines code under three closely related BSD-3-clause
style licenses, each preserved verbatim in the LICENSES/ directory.
All three permit redistribution + modification with attribution and
require source availability for binary releases.

Components and their licenses:

1. New files under machdep/pegasos2/ (this project's clean-room
   rewrite) and the project-level documentation:

       Copyright (c) 2026 Pegasos2 clean-room rewrite contributors.
       All rights reserved.

   Released under the CodeGen SmartFirmware source license
   (BSD-3-clause-style + source-availability clause). Full text:
   LICENSES/CodeGen-smartfirmware.txt.

2. Vendored upstream/smartfirmware/ tree (the SmartFirmware OF
   runtime that this project sits atop):

       Copyright (c) 1992-2005 CodeGen, Inc. All rights reserved.

   Released under the same CodeGen license as (1).
   Full text: LICENSES/CodeGen-smartfirmware.txt.
   Source provenance: upstream/smartfirmware/COPYRIGHT.

3. Vendored upstream/x86emu/ tree (the x86 real-mode emulator
   used to execute PCI option ROMs):

       Copyright (c) 1996-1999 SciTech Software, Inc.
       Copyright (c) David Mosberger-Tang
       Copyright (c) 1999 Egbert Eich
       Copyright (c) Freescale Semiconductor, Inc. (Jason Jin)

   Released under the SciTech x86 Realmode Emulator Library
   license (BSD-3-clause-style). Full text:
   LICENSES/SciTech-x86emu.txt.

   Only the SciTech-licensed realmode emulator core
   (upstream/x86emu/x86emu/*.c and the x86emu/*.h headers) is
   vendored. The U-Boot bios_emulator wrapper files that lived
   alongside it in the original U-Boot tree (besys.c, atibios.c,
   vesa.c, vesa.h) were GPL-2.0-only or carried no licence
   header and have been removed from this tree to keep the
   source bundle GPL-free; the Pegasos II firmware never
   referenced them.

Full-text license files
-----------------------

For the complete text of each license, including the
source-availability clause that applies to clauses (1) and (2),
see:

  LICENSES/CodeGen-smartfirmware.txt
  LICENSES/SciTech-x86emu.txt

Each source file in this tree carries a license header pointing at
one of the above; vendored files retain their original headers
verbatim.

Binary-distribution obligation
------------------------------

Per clause 3 of the CodeGen license, binary releases of this
firmware must be accompanied by either (a) the complete source
code, or (b) a written offer to provide the source for no more
than the cost of distribution plus a nominal fee. The source
must be freely redistributable under reasonable conditions.

This project's GitHub releases satisfy clause 3 by publishing
the complete source tree alongside every binary asset.
